Siemens Managers Arrested on Corruption Allegations, FTD Reports

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-06-09T18:59:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/siemens-managers-arrested-on-corruption-allegations-ftd-reports.html
German prosecutors arrested two
 Siemens AG (SIE)  managers, who had worked in  Kuwait , on corruption
allegations, and issued an arrest warrant against a third,
Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing people in the
justice sector without naming them.  Barbara Stockinger, a spokeswoman for the Munich
prosecutors, didn’t immediately return a call to her mobile
phone. Siemens spokesman Joern Roggenbuck declined to comment
“on current investigations.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  